quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  7,12,"Allah said, "What stopped you from prostrating when I ordered you?" He said, "I am better than him. You have created me of fire, and created him of clay.""
  7,13,"He said, "Then, go down from here, it is not for you to be arrogant here. So, go. You are of the low.""
  7,14,"He said, "Then give me respite until a day when all will be resurrected.""
  7,15,"He (Allah) said, "Respite is given to you.""
  7,16,"He said, "Then as You have made me go astray, I swear that I will sit for them (in ambush) on Your straight path."
  7,17,"Then I will come upon them from in front of them and from behind them and from their right and from their left. And you will not find most of them grateful."
  7,18,"He (Allah) said, "Get out of here, condemned, rejected. Indeed, those of them who follow you, I will fill Hell with you all together."
  7,19,"And 0 'Adam, dwell, you and your wife, in Paradise, and eat from wherever you like, but do not go near this tree, otherwise you shall join the transgressors.""
  7,20,"Then Satan whispered to them, so that he may uncover to them what was covered of their shame; and said, "Your Lord has not prohibited this tree for you, but to avoid your becoming angels or your becoming eternal.""
  7,21,"And he swore on oaths, "I am one of your well-wishers.""
  7,22,"So he cast them down by deception. So, when they tasted (the fruit of) the tree, their shame be-came apparent to them, and they began to patch together upon themselves some leaves of Paradise, and their Lord called them, "Did I not forbid you from that tree, and did I not tell you that the Satan is an open enemy for you?""